parameters.name: ExecutionNamePrefix
parameters.description: The name prefix of the execution.

parameters.name: FlowName
parameters.description:
The name of the flow. The name must be unique within the region and cannot be modified after the flow is created. The name must meet the following conventions:

*   The name can contain letters, digits, underscores (\_), and hyphens (-).
*   The name must start with a letter or an underscore (\_).
*   The name is case-sensitive.
*   The name must be 1 to 128 characters in length.

parameters.name: Limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of executions to be queried. Valid values: 1 to 100.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description: The name of the execution to start the query. You can obtain the value from the response data. You do not need to specify this parameter for the first request.

parameters.name: RequestId
parameters.description: The request ID. If you specify this parameter, the system uses this value as the ID of the request. If you do not specify this parameter, the system generates a value at random.

parameters.name: StartedTimeBegin
parameters.description: The beginning of the time range to query executions. Specify the value in the UTC RFC3339 format.

parameters.name: StartedTimeEnd
parameters.description: The end of the time range to query executions. Specify the value in the UTC RFC3339 format.

parameters.name: Status
parameters.description:
The state of the execution that you want to filter. Valid values:

*   **Running**
*   **Stopped**
*   **Succeeded**
*   **Failed**
*   **TimedOut**
